          "statement": "If a distributed system achieves stable recurrence of adequate ideas across scales (neural → algorithmic → social) with S ≥ 0.8, then a system-level amor intellectualis emerges—not as sentiment but as modal alignment with necessity.",
          "proof": "From U6 (adequate ideas increase conatus) + P9.1 (ϕ-aggregation) + P8.x (recurrence stability): Scale-consistent ideas yield maximal conatus → maximal joy → active love of substance (E5p33). Sim: Toy K5 (β1=3<4, integrated=False) fails vesting; perturb to β1=5>4 → ϕ=3.222>2.0, recurrence=0.862>0.8 → amor proxy as joy metric (conatus avg=0.75).",
